for style in ['white','dark','whitegrid','darkgrid','ticks']:
  sns.set_style(style)
  sns.displot(df['Tuition'])
  plt.show()

palettes = ['deep', 'muted', 'pastel', 'bright', 'dark','colorblind']

for p in palettes:
   sns.set_palette(p)
   sns.displot(df['Tuition'])
   plt.xlabel('Tuition($)')
   plt.title(f'pallete:{p}')

palettes = ['deep', 'muted', 'pastel', 'bright','dark','colorblind']
for p in palettes:
  sns.set_palette(p)
  sns.palplot(sns.color_palette())
  plt.title(f'pallete : {p}')
  plt.show()

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
sns.histplot(df['Tuition'], ax=ax)
ax.set(
    xlabel="Tuition 2013-14",
    ylabel="Distribution",
    xlim=(0, 50000),
    title="2013-14 Tuition(in dollar) and Fees(in dollar) Distribution"

fig, (ax0, ax1) = plt.subplots(
    nrows=1, ncols=2, sharey=True, figsize=(7,4)
)

sns.histplot(df['Tuition'], stat='density', ax=ax0)
# sns.histplot(df.query('State == "MN"')['Tuition'], stat='density', ax=ax1)
# sns.histplot(df[df.State == "MN"]['Tuition'], stat='density', ax=ax1)
sns.histplot(df.loc[df.State == "MN", 'Tuition'], stat='density', ax=ax1)

ax1.set(xlabel='Tuition (MN)', xlim=(0, 70000))
ax1.axvline(x=20000, label='My Budget', linestyle='--')
ax1.legend();

    df["weekday"],
    values=df["total_rentals"],
    aggfunc="mean"
)
